						<summary>

						<p>Pillar set up at the entrance into the compound of the Chennakēśava svāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>956 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This archaic record is dated Śaka 878, (in words) uttarāyaṇa, corresponding 956 A.D.</p>						

						<p>Registers the gift of 8 <hi rend="italic">marturus</hi> of land located in front of the temple of Bhaṭāra by Bijja[ṇa], the rule of the village Gōḻūru to Gaṭṭyabōya, son of Kāṭaya raḍḍi. The inscriptions is engraved by Vīrāchāri.</p>						

						</summary>
